<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-e5dbbdb elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="e5dbbdb" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">Recommended Experience</h3>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-962fd21 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="962fd21" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<p>Dyeing Experience, Lake Kawaguchi, Grapes, Plant-Based Dyeing, Pumice</p>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-dcd1d79 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-id="dcd1d79" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="image.default"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="attachment-large size-large wp-image-2445" src="../assets/pamis-1024x574.png" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="../assets/pamis-1024x574.png 1024w, ../assets/pamis-300x168.png 300w, ../assets/pamis-768x430.png 768w, ../assets/pamis-320x180.png 320w, ../assets/pamis.png 1456w" alt="" width="1024" height="574"></div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-14b79cc elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="14b79cc" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<h3 data-start="580" data-end="596"><strong data-start="584" data-end="596">Overview</strong></h3>
<p data-start="597" data-end="1030">In this dyeing experience, participants use <strong data-start="641" data-end="665">grape skins (pumice)</strong> and flowers to create their own unique works while enjoying the natural beauty of plant-based colors.<br data-start="767" data-end="770">The <strong data-start="774" data-end="804">vivid yet gentle pink tone</strong> is especially popular with women and children.<br data-start="851" data-end="854">The process is simple, making it safe and enjoyable even for <strong data-start="915" data-end="947">young children and beginners</strong>.<br data-start="948" data-end="951">It’s a perfect activity to create <strong data-start="985" data-end="1029">lasting memories with family and friends</strong>!</p>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-4fb2e14 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="4fb2e14" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<h3 data-start="1037" data-end="1060"><strong data-start="1041" data-end="1060">Important Notes</strong></h3>
<p data-start="252" data-end="393">The color of wine-dyed fabrics may change to light blue, purple, or pink, depending on environmental conditions.</p>
<p data-start="401" data-end="580">This is caused by anthocyanin, a natural pigment found in grapes—the main ingredient in wine. The final color can vary based on pH levels and temperature during or after dyeing.</p>
<ul data-start="1311" data-end="1608">
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul data-start="1311" data-end="1608">
<li data-start="588" data-end="666">
<p data-start="590" data-end="666">Using <strong data-start="596" data-end="617">neutral detergent</strong> will give the fabric a <strong data-start="641" data-end="658">purplish pink</strong> tone.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="669" data-end="739">
<p data-start="671" data-end="739">Using a <strong data-start="679" data-end="708">mildly alkaline detergent</strong> will turn it <strong data-start="722" data-end="736">light blue</strong>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul data-start="1311" data-end="1608">
<li data-start="742" data-end="894">
<p data-start="744" data-end="894">To <strong data-start="747" data-end="772">preserve the pink hue</strong>, use a <strong data-start="780" data-end="807">mildly acidic detergent</strong>, or soak the item in water mixed with <strong data-start="846" data-end="861">citric acid</strong> after washing and before drying.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-713f999 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent" data-id="713f999" data-element_type="container">
<div class="e-con-inner">
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-7085ac5 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child" data-id="7085ac5" data-element_type="container">
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-52c7d03 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="52c7d03" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
<h2 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">Workshop Flow</h2>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-4ef3655 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="4ef3655" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<p>The pattern created during the dyeing experience is determined by how you tie the T-shirt.<br data-start="90" data-end="93">Please decide in advance what kind of pattern you would like to make before starting the dyeing process.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-2544aa1 e-grid e-con-boxed e-con e-parent" data-id="2544aa1" data-element_type="container">
<div class="e-con-inner">
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-e67056f elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-id="e67056f" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="image.default"></div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-ff4c267 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-id="ff4c267" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="image.default"></div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-5d51e68 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="5d51e68" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">1.Arrival &amp; Check-in</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="attachment-large size-large wp-image-2444" src="../assets/Workshop-Exterior-1024x683.jpg" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="../assets/Workshop-Exterior-1024x683.jpg 1024w, ../assets/Workshop-Exterior-300x200.jpg 300w, ../assets/Workshop-Exterior-768x512.jpg 768w, ../assets/Workshop-Exterior.jpg 1536w" alt="" width="1024" height="683"></p>
<p>Please arrive at least 5 minutes before your scheduled time.<br data-start="200" data-end="203">Check-in takes place at our sister shop “Fujiya,” located just across the street.<br data-start="284" data-end="287">Once you arrive, please enter the shop and complete the check-in process.<br data-start="360" data-end="363">A staff member will guide you to the workshop after that.</p>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-c6af36c elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="c6af36c" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">2.Introduction</h3>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-1bbae50 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="1bbae50" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="attachment-large size-large wp-image-2443" src="../assets/Pre-Workshop-Instructions-1024x682.jpg" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="../assets/Pre-Workshop-Instructions-1024x682.jpg 1024w, ../assets/Pre-Workshop-Instructions-300x200.jpg 300w, ../assets/Pre-Workshop-Instructions-768x512.jpg 768w, ../assets/Pre-Workshop-Instructions.jpg 1477w" alt="" width="1024" height="682"></p>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-43c76f3 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="43c76f3" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<p>You’ll be welcomed by our staff, who will introduce the workshop and explain how the dyeing process works.<br data-start="249" data-end="252">In addition to creating your own piece, you’ll also learn about <strong data-start="316" data-end="386">the unique pumice dyeing method rooted in Yamanashi’s wine culture</strong>, as well as the <strong data-start="403" data-end="466">history and beauty of traditional Japanese dyes like indigo</strong>.<br data-start="467" data-end="470">It’s more than just a craft—it’s a chance to connect with local tradition and sustainable practices.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-4bb0b78 e-grid e-con-boxed e-con e-parent" data-id="4bb0b78" data-element_type="container">
<div class="e-con-inner">
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-6a21d7f elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-id="6a21d7f" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="image.default"></div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-5ee6d5d elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="5ee6d5d" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">3.Choose Your Dye</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="attachment-large size-large wp-image-2442" src="../assets/Choosing-Dye-Materials-1024x682.jpg" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="../assets/Choosing-Dye-Materials-1024x682.jpg 1024w, ../assets/Choosing-Dye-Materials-300x200.jpg 300w, ../assets/Choosing-Dye-Materials-768x512.jpg 768w, ../assets/Choosing-Dye-Materials.jpg 1477w" alt="" width="1024" height="682"></p>
<p>You can choose from three types of dyes:<br data-start="157" data-end="160"><strong data-start="160" data-end="170">Pumice</strong> (made from grape skins), <strong data-start="196" data-end="206">Indigo</strong> (a traditional Japanese blue dye), or <strong data-start="245" data-end="253">Sumi</strong> (black ink dye).<br data-start="270" data-end="273">If you are joining as a group, each person may select their preferred dye individually.</p>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-cd6e67f elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="cd6e67f" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">4.Choose Your Pattern</h3>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-4dc307b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="4dc307b" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="attachment-large size-large wp-image-2441" src="../assets/Choosing-Dyeing-Patterns-1024x682.jpg" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="../assets/Choosing-Dyeing-Patterns-1024x682.jpg 1024w, ../assets/Choosing-Dyeing-Patterns-300x200.jpg 300w, ../assets/Choosing-Dyeing-Patterns-768x512.jpg 768w, ../assets/Choosing-Dyeing-Patterns.jpg 1477w" alt="" width="1024" height="682"></p>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-5f1d01b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="5f1d01b" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<p>Next, choose your preferred dyeing technique.<br data-start="141" data-end="144">Our experienced staff will guide you through various options such as spiral tie-dye, <em data-start="229" data-end="239">murakumo</em> (cloud-like patterns), cylinder wrapping, or rubber band tie-dye.<br data-start="305" data-end="308">You can even combine multiple techniques to create your own unique design.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-8a24d97 e-grid e-con-boxed e-con e-parent" data-id="8a24d97" data-element_type="container">
<div class="e-con-inner">
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-3edd0ba elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-id="3edd0ba" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="image.default"></div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-d17536c elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-id="d17536c" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="image.default"></div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-0b8dd3c elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="0b8dd3c" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">5.Prepare &amp; Bind Your T-Shirt</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="attachment-large size-large wp-image-2440" src="../assets/Binding-T-Shirts-for-Tie-Dye-1024x682.jpg" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="../assets/Binding-T-Shirts-for-Tie-Dye-1024x682.jpg 1024w, ../assets/Binding-T-Shirts-for-Tie-Dye-300x200.jpg 300w, ../assets/Binding-T-Shirts-for-Tie-Dye-768x512.jpg 768w, ../assets/Binding-T-Shirts-for-Tie-Dye.jpg 1477w" alt="" width="1024" height="682"></p>
<p>Soak your T-shirt in water to help the dye absorb better.<br data-start="194" data-end="197">Then, bind it tightly using strings, rubber bands, or sticks.<br data-start="258" data-end="261">If the binding is too loose, the dye will seep in too deeply, making it difficult to form clear patterns.<br data-start="366" data-end="369">Since this step can require some strength, we recommend that children work together with an adult.</p>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-f7a04a5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="f7a04a5" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">6.Dye Bath</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="attachment-large size-large wp-image-2439" src="../assets/Soaking-T-Shirts-in-Dye-Bath-1024x682.jpg" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="../assets/Soaking-T-Shirts-in-Dye-Bath-1024x682.jpg 1024w, ../assets/Soaking-T-Shirts-in-Dye-Bath-300x200.jpg 300w, ../assets/Soaking-T-Shirts-in-Dye-Bath-768x512.jpg 768w, ../assets/Soaking-T-Shirts-in-Dye-Bath.jpg 1477w" alt="" width="1024" height="682"></p>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-53cd0b5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="53cd0b5" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<p>After tightly binding your shirt with strings or rubber bands, you’ll submerge it in a large container filled with your chosen dye.<br data-start="281" data-end="284">Each dye requires a different soaking time—indigo takes just a few minutes, while sumi needs about 10 minutes.<br data-start="394" data-end="397">While you wait, imagine how the colors and patterns will turn out!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-f604b6a e-grid e-con-boxed e-con e-parent" data-id="f604b6a" data-element_type="container">
<div class="e-con-inner">
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-4aed896 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-id="4aed896" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="image.default"></div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-08bcb2b elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-id="08bcb2b" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="image.default"></div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-7361fba elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="7361fba" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">7.Rinse &amp; Reveal</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="attachment-large size-large wp-image-2438" src="../assets/Rinsing-Dyed-T-Shirts-1024x682.jpg" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="../assets/Rinsing-Dyed-T-Shirts-1024x682.jpg 1024w, ../assets/Rinsing-Dyed-T-Shirts-300x200.jpg 300w, ../assets/Rinsing-Dyed-T-Shirts-768x512.jpg 768w, ../assets/Rinsing-Dyed-T-Shirts.jpg 1477w" alt="" width="1024" height="682"></p>
<p>When the dyeing time is up, remove all strings and rubber bands.<br data-start="212" data-end="215">Rinse your shirt thoroughly with water to remove excess dye—but not too much or too little, as either can affect how clearly the pattern appears.<br data-start="360" data-end="363">After rinsing, wring out the fabric well to remove excess water.</p>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-eb853f5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="eb853f5" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">8.Unfold &amp; Admire</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="attachment-large size-large wp-image-2437" src="../assets/Finished-Dyed-T-Shirts.jpg" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="../assets/Finished-Dyed-T-Shirts.jpg 1024w, ../assets/Finished-Dyed-T-Shirts-300x200.jpg 300w, ../assets/Finished-Dyed-T-Shirts-768x512.jpg 768w" alt="" width="1024" height="683"></p>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-4a5ce64 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="4a5ce64" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<p>Unfold your T-shirt and take a look!</p>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-1c23e90 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="1c23e90" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<p data-start="115" data-end="391">Your one-of-a-kind design is now complete.<br data-start="221" data-end="224">Some results may match your original image, while others might surprise you—but that’s the charm of hand-dyeing.<br data-start="336" data-end="339">Whatever the outcome, it’s your own unique creation.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-9f59a03 e-grid e-con-boxed e-con e-parent" data-id="9f59a03" data-element_type="container">
<div class="e-con-inner">
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-e889ce9 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-id="e889ce9" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="image.default"></div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-3e52f04 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-id="3e52f04" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="image.default"></div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-ac52949 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="ac52949" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">9.Photo Time &amp; Memories</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="attachment-large size-large wp-image-2436" src="../assets/Group-Photo-with-Finished-Creations-1024x682.jpg" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="../assets/Group-Photo-with-Finished-Creations-1024x682.jpg 1024w, ../assets/Group-Photo-with-Finished-Creations-300x200.jpg 300w, ../assets/Group-Photo-with-Finished-Creations-768x512.jpg 768w, ../assets/Group-Photo-with-Finished-Creations.jpg 1373w" alt="" width="1024" height="682"></p>
<p>After completing your shirt, take photos together with your fellow participants!</p>
<p>Crafted at the foot of Mt. Fuji using its underground spring water, your creation makes the perfect souvenir from your trip to Yamanashi.</p>
<p>For kids, it’s a hands-on learning experience—and for adults, a joyful moment to relive childhood excitement.</p>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-0d98c7b elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="0d98c7b" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">10.Final Notes &amp; Take-Home Care</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="attachment-large size-large wp-image-2435" src="../assets/ce5ae462.jpeg" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="../assets/ce5ae462.jpeg 1024w, ../assets/6745c817.jpeg 300w, ../assets/6191b4c9.jpeg 768w" alt="" width="1024" height="683"></p>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-8a6675f elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="8a6675f" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<p>Before you leave, we’ll give you a take-home care guide for your shirt.</p>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-dbd696f elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="dbd696f" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<p>It includes tips on how to wash and care for your dyed item at home.<br data-start="282" data-end="285">We also sell dye kits in-store, so you can refresh your shirt’s color later or try dyeing something else!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h2 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">Reservations</h2>
<div class="widget widget_vkexunit_contact_section">
<div class="veu_contact">
<section class="veu_contact veu_contentAddSection">
