<li data-start="151" data-end="251">
<p data-start="154" data-end="251"><strong data-start="154" data-end="207">Send Your Preferred Date &amp; Number of Participants</strong><br data-start="207" data-end="210">Please check the calendar for availability before sending your request.<br data-start="450" data-end="453"><strong data-start="453" data-end="518">Same-day bookings are not guaranteed and may not be accepted.</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="253" data-end="533">
<p data-start="256" data-end="533"><strong data-start="256" data-end="280">Receive Confirmation</strong><br data-start="280" data-end="283">In addition to the dyeing workshop, we also offer a cooking experience where you can make and enjoy Yamanashi specialties such as houtou (a local noodle stew) and soba.<br data-start="718" data-end="721">Feel free to add this to your visit for a complete cultural experience.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="535" data-end="609">
<p data-start="538" data-end="609"><strong data-start="538" data-end="553">Pay On-Site</strong><br data-start="553" data-end="556">Payment can be made on-site by <strong data-start="846" data-end="904">cash, credit card, or QR code</strong>.</p>
</li>
