<section id="faq" class="tsl-faq">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<p>Here are some of the most common questions about our dyeing workshops. If you don’t find your answer, please feel free to contact us anytime.</p>

<details>
<summary>Can I only dye T-shirts?</summary>
<div class="answer">No. We also provide hand towels, stoles, and other items for dyeing.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Can children join the workshop?</summary>
<div class="answer">Yes. The activity is safe and fun for children. Parents or guardians are welcome to join together.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Are there less crowded times?</summary>
<div class="answer">Weekdays are usually quieter than weekends and holidays.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Can I join without a reservation?</summary>
<div class="answer">Walk-ins are welcome if space is available, but we recommend advance booking to secure your spot.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Do you provide English support?</summary>
<div class="answer">Yes. English-speaking staff are available to assist you.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Can I participate if I have nail extensions or polish?</summary>
<div class="answer">Yes. No problem. We can provide gloves if needed.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Can I pay by credit card?</summary>
<div class="answer">Yes. We accept credit cards and cash.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>How far is the workshop from Lake Kawaguchi?</summary>
<div class="answer">It is just a few minutes by car from Lake Kawaguchi.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>How long does it take to walk from the nearest station?</summary>
<div class="answer">About 10 minutes on foot from Kawaguchiko Station.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Is parking available?</summary>
<div class="answer">Yes. We have free parking spaces for visitors.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Can tour buses park at the workshop?</summary>
<div class="answer">Yes. Tour buses are welcome with prior reservation.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Can I make a reservation late at night or early in the morning?</summary>
<div class="answer">Yes. Online reservations are available 24/7.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Is a reservation required?</summary>
<div class="answer">Advance booking is recommended to guarantee availability.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>What is the maximum group size for the workshop?</summary>
<div class="answer">We can welcome groups of up to 50 participants. Please contact us for larger groups.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Do I need to bring anything?</summary>
<div class="answer">No. All materials and tools are provided. Please wear clothes that can get a little dyed.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Can I wear my indigo-dyed clothing right away?</summary>
<div class="answer">Yes. After rinsing and drying, you can wear it the same day.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Will the colors fade in the wash?</summary>
<div class="answer">Some fading may occur over time. Wash separately in cold water for the first few washes.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Can I take photos or videos during the workshop?</summary>
<div class="answer">Yes. Photos and videos are welcome.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Is the workshop available on rainy days?</summary>
<div class="answer">Yes. The workshop is held indoors and is all-weather friendly.</div>
</details>
<p class="muted">Tip: If you have any special requests (on-site workshops, large groups, language support), please contact us in advance.</p>
</section>
